@page "/projects"

<PageTitle>Projects | Zone 55</PageTitle>

<section class="hero about-hero container-xl">
    <div class="hero-main">
        <div class="eyebrow">
            <span></span>
            Portfolio project
        </div>

        <h1>
            Projects<br />
            <span>systems I build and document</span>
        </h1>

        <p>
            This section connects the blog content with real implementation: backend structure,
            cloud deployment, CI/CD, diagrams, and practical engineering decisions.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="content-frame container-xl">
    <section class="posts-area about-content">
        <div class="section-kicker">MAIN PROJECT</div>

        <h2>Blog Platform</h2>

        <p>
            This site is more than a blog. It is a portfolio system used to show how I structure,
            document, and evolve a .NET backend + cloud-oriented application.
        </p>

        <div class="project-grid">
            <div class="project-card">
                <h3>Backend</h3>
                <p>ASP.NET Core application structure, API thinking, DTOs, configuration, and maintainable boundaries.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="project-card">
                <h3>Cloud</h3>
                <p>Azure-ready deployment approach with environment-based configuration and secret management.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="project-card">
                <h3>DevOps</h3>
                <p>CI/CD pipeline direction using GitHub Actions or Azure DevOps for build, test, and deployment.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="project-card">
                <h3>Architecture</h3>
                <p>PlantUML diagrams, system documentation, and design notes explaining technical decisions.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Planned article series</h3>

        <ul>
            <li>Architecture of this blog platform</li>
            <li>How I structure configuration in ASP.NET Core</li>
            <li>CI/CD pipeline for a .NET application</li>
            <li>Deploying ASP.NET Core to Azure</li>
            <li>Using PlantUML to document backend architecture</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</section>
